16:09.850 --> 16:12.119
[Door closes]

16:14.822 --> 16:16.623
Excuse me.

16:16.624 --> 16:18.259
I'm about to be spontaneous.

16:20.327 --> 16:22.062
Oh. Velcro.

16:22.063 --> 16:24.130
I did not know they were detachable.

16:24.131 --> 16:25.331
Smart design.

16:25.332 --> 16:27.234
[Sighs]

16:36.277 --> 16:38.645
[Gasps] Oh, my God! Mike, it's happening!

16:38.646 --> 16:40.647
He went in early, like Axl said.

16:40.648 --> 16:41.915
Hey, that's my boy.

16:41.916 --> 16:44.884
Oh, wow. They're still going.

16:44.885 --> 16:47.154
And they're still going.

16:57.598 --> 16:59.699
Mike, we did teach him about stopping,
right?

16:59.700 --> 17:01.201
I didn't think we had to.

17:01.202 --> 17:02.302
I think we had to.

17:02.303 --> 17:04.304
I mean,
they're not even moving their heads.

17:04.305 --> 17:05.605
They're like statues.

17:05.606 --> 17:08.340
Look at her neck. That's got to hurt.

17:08.342 --> 17:09.709
Frankie, I think we should break this up.

17:09.710 --> 17:11.778
No, that'll be embarrassing.

17:11.779 --> 17:13.847
Maybe we should just go out to the car.

17:13.848 --> 17:16.549
You know, when they see us,
they'll probably stop.

17:16.550 --> 17:17.784
What are we going out there for?

17:17.785 --> 17:19.752
We'll just say we're going to Walgreens.

17:21.555 --> 17:23.190
[Clears throat]

17:24.791 --> 17:26.659
Mike, did you lock the door?

17:26.660 --> 17:28.595
Yes, I did.

17:28.596 --> 17:30.630
What did you want to get from Walgreens?

17:30.631 --> 17:32.132
Uh, we need toilet paper.

17:32.133 --> 17:33.300
Oh, yeah.

17:40.875 --> 17:42.943
[Engine turns over]

17:44.778 --> 17:45.813
Now what?

17:47.014 --> 17:49.749
Well, we do need toilet paper.

17:49.750 --> 17:51.585
Guess we're going to Walgreens.

18:12.072 --> 18:13.573
There's my Valentine!

18:13.574 --> 18:14.641
[Squeals]

18:14.642 --> 18:16.342
Darrin! Ooh!

18:16.343 --> 18:19.045
This has just been the best day ever!

18:19.046 --> 18:21.681
All the clues,
and everybody's been so nice.

18:21.682 --> 18:24.184
Well, the manager at
the Bowling Alley had a little 'tude,

18:24.185 --> 18:26.052
but there were four parties going on today,

18:26.053 --> 18:27.153
so I totally get it.

18:27.154 --> 18:28.288
But I can't believe

18:28.289 --> 18:30.156
you set up all these
things in all these places,

18:30.157 --> 18:31.858
and I don't even know where we are now.

18:31.859 --> 18:33.126
Where are we?

18:33.127 --> 18:35.229
The last stop in your Scavenger Hunt.
Come in.

18:38.132 --> 18:39.632
Surprise!

18:39.633 --> 18:41.067
Welcome to my house.

18:41.068 --> 18:42.101
What?

18:42.102 --> 18:43.770
Well, you know, I've been working hard

18:43.771 --> 18:45.572
and saving my air-conditioning money,

18:45.573 --> 18:46.606
so I bought this house.

18:46.607 --> 18:48.308
Just closed on it yesterday.

18:48.309 --> 18:49.809
Oh, wow.

18:49.810 --> 18:52.045
I mean... Wow!

18:52.046 --> 18:54.080
It's great,
'cause the kitchen and the living room

18:54.081 --> 18:56.183
are in the same room,
and back there's the bedroom.

19:02.623 --> 19:06.092
It's nice how the bed
touches all four walls.

19:06.093 --> 19:08.761
Yeah. Now I never have to worry
about falling off the bed.

19:08.762 --> 19:10.063
[Laughs]

19:10.064 --> 19:13.967
And look...
this folds down into a kitchen table.

19:13.968 --> 19:16.069
These fold into seats.

19:16.070 --> 19:17.136
Oh.

19:17.137 --> 19:20.807
And this folds down into a couch.

19:20.808 --> 19:22.076
Ah.

19:23.978 --> 19:27.114
Do any of them fold down into a sweater?

19:33.120 --> 19:34.988
You know, today is Valentine's day,

19:34.989 --> 19:37.257
and we haven't even
talked about you and me.

19:37.258 --> 19:38.558
Yeah, well, you know.

19:38.559 --> 19:41.227
So... I got you a little something.

19:41.228 --> 19:42.328
Aww.

19:42.329 --> 19:45.632
Well, it just so happens I got
you a little something, too.

19:45.633 --> 19:48.635
- What?
- Mm-hmm.

19:48.636 --> 19:51.638
Hey! Sports Illustrated. Thank you.

19:51.639 --> 19:53.840
Ooh! French onion Pringles!

19:53.841 --> 19:55.842
Guess you're not gonna be
kissing me tonight, hm?

19:55.843 --> 19:56.843
[Chuckles]

19:56.844 --> 19:58.878
Ooh! You got the Tweezers I wanted!

19:58.879 --> 20:01.214
Yeah, well,
you've been mentioning it, so...

20:01.215 --> 20:03.816
All right!
A giant remote so I can see the numbers!

20:03.817 --> 20:05.084
[Chuckles]

20:05.085 --> 20:06.686
Aww.

20:06.687 --> 20:08.054
And you always say

20:08.055 --> 20:11.090
how embarrassed you are
to go into the lady aisle.

20:11.091 --> 20:12.558
Happy Valentine's day, Frankie.

20:12.559 --> 20:15.328
Mmm. Happy Valentine's day.

20:15.329 --> 20:18.331
So, you think it's safe to go home?

20:18.332 --> 20:21.601
Yeah. They got to be done by now.

20:21.602 --> 20:23.303
Wow, Darrin.

20:23.304 --> 20:26.072
Well, you're a homeowner. Congratulations.

20:26.073 --> 20:28.107
This is so exciting for you.

20:28.108 --> 20:31.210
Actually, Sue, there's one more surprise.

20:31.211 --> 20:32.812
The house isn't mine.

20:32.813 --> 20:34.180
It isn't?

20:34.181 --> 20:35.181
No.

20:35.182 --> 20:37.017
It's ours.

20:42.323 --> 20:44.625
Sue Heck, will you marry me?

21:11.618 --> 21:13.619
Okay. You're done.

21:13.620 --> 21:16.856
Happy Valentine's day, Cindy.

21:16.857 --> 21:18.158
Nailed it.

